\lim_{x \to \infty} \sqrt{9x^2+x} - 3x
9x^2
\sqrt{1+x}=1+\frac{x}{2}+O(x^2)
 \begin{align} \lim_{x\to\infty}(\sqrt{9x^2+x}-3x)&=\lim_{x\to\infty}3x\left(\sqrt{1+\frac{1}{9x}}-1\right)\\ &=\lim_{x\to\infty}3x\left(\frac{1}{18x}+O\left(\frac{1}{x^2}\right)\right)\\ &=\frac{1}{6} \end{align} 
\lim\limits_{x\to +\infty} \sqrt{9x^2+x}-3x
x=1/h
x\to +\infty
h\to 0^+
\lim_{x\to +\infty} \sqrt{9x^2+x}-3x= \lim_{h\to 0^+} \sqrt{\frac{9}{h^2}+\frac{1}{h}}-\frac{3}{h} = \lim_{h\to 0^+} \sqrt{\frac{1}{h^2}(9+h)}-\frac{3}{h} = \lim_{h\to 0^+} \frac{\sqrt{9+h}-3}{h}= \frac{1}{6}
